asic routes expose all enabled tools/resources/prompts.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-resources-prompts.md:17:- OAuth Bearer routes expose only the enabled tools/resources/prompts included in the token permissions.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-resources-prompts.md:18:- Unknown, disabled, or unauthorized resources/prompts never leak content. Authentication failures remain `401`; valid Bearer tokens without permission return `403`.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-resources-prompts.md:23:  - `resources: { subscribe: true, listChanged: true }`\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-resources-prompts.md:26:- `resources/list` returns enabled direct resources, supports cursor pagination, and includes URI, name, title, description, MIME type, size, and annotations when present.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-resources-prompts.md:27:- `resources/templates/list` returns enabled templates with URI template, name, title, description, MIME type, and annotations when present.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-resources-prompts.md:28:- `resources/read` returns text or blob contents for a direct URI or a rendered template URI.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-resources-prompts.md:29:- `resources/subscribe` and `resources/unsubscribe` are supported only for live legacy SSE sessions and return empty success results for valid accessible resources.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-resources-prompts.md:31:- `prompts/get` validates required arguments and returns ordered prompt messages with substituted text and optional embedded resource content.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-resources-prompts.md:32:- `completion/complete` supports `ref/prompt` by prompt name and `ref/resource` by URI template.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-resources-prompts.md:33:- Resource-not-found errors use JSON-RPC `-32002`; invalid params use `-32602`; unsupported methods continue to use `-32601`.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-resources-prompts.md:36:- Add `Resources`, `Resource Templates`, and `Prompts` under the Tools group.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-resources-prompts.md:40:- Beginner-facing tooltips explain resources as application-controlled context and prompts as user-controlled templates.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-resources-prompts.md:43:- OAuth clients define allowed tools, resources, and prompts.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-resources-prompts.md:44:- Authorization codes store selected tool/resource/prompt permissions.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-resources-prompts.md:46:- Consent UI groups permission checklists by Tools, Resources, and Prompts and makes selected scope unambiguous.\ndocs/product-specs/mcp-resources-prompts.md:50:- E2E covers admin CRUD, MCP no-auth/Basic/OAuth list/read/get/complete, OAuth consent denial, SSE resource update notifications, and Inspector scenario evidence.\ntests/e2e/token-revocation.spec.ts:59:        resource: \"https://resource.example/token-revocation\",\ndocs/INSPECTOR.md:96:- health, operator config, OAuth discovery metadata, protected-resource metadata, and JWKS\ndocs/INSPECTOR.md:210:3. Add an opt-in OAuth resource strict mode so clients can verify audience/resource mismatches before integrating with production services.\ndocs/INSPECTOR.md:211:4. Add Docker/Nginx discovery smoke coverage for forwarded host/proto, `APP_BASE_URL`, OAuth metadata, and Bearer `resource_metadata` correctness behind a proxy.\ndocs/exec-plans/active/index.md:7:1. `027-mcp-resource-prompt-domain-schema.md` -> `mcp-resource-prompt-domain-schema` -> Add persistence, seed defaults, validators, and services for Resources, Resource Templates, Prompts, and Completion candidates.\ndocs/exec-plans/active/index.md:8:2. `028-mcp-resource-management-ui.md` -> `mcp-resource-management-ui` -> Add direct Resource admin UI/API workflows with focused catalog/detail pages.\ndocs/exec-plans/active/index.md:9:3. `029-mcp-resource-template-management-ui.md` -> `mcp-resource-template-management-ui` -> Add Resource Template admin UI/API workflows with arguments, rendered content, and completion candidates.\ndocs/exec-plans/active/index.md:10:4. `030-mcp-prompt-management-u